<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Zend_Dojo_Form_Element_Editor create textarea which not recommended as the dojo docs says "RichText should not be used with the TEXTAREA tag.  See dijit._editor.RichText docs"</p>

<p>Anyway, the form post data as array and the form declare single element.</p>

<p>Here is a test case working fine on Firefox, please test it on IE.</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
class PartnerForm extends Zend_Dojo_Form
{

    public function __construct()
    {
        parent::__construct();
        
        $name = new Zend_Form_Element_Text('name');
        $name-&gt;setLabel('Partner Name:');
        $name-&gt;addFilter('StringTrim');
        $name-&gt;setRequired(true);
        $name-&gt;addValidator(new Zend_Validate_Alnum(true));
        $name-&gt;addValidator('StringLength', false, array(3 , 60));
        
        $homepage = new Zend_Form_Element_Text('homepage');
        $homepage-&gt;setLabel('Homepage:');
        $homepage-&gt;addFilter('StringTrim');
        
        $desc = new Zend_Dojo_Form_Element_Editor('description');
        $desc-&gt;setLabel('Description:');
        $this-&gt;setMethod("post");
        $this-&gt;setAttrib('enctype', 'multipart/form-data');
    }
}
</code></pre>

<p>My test was on IE 7</p>

